What is the most powerful in the United Nations? The most powerful individual in the United Nations is the President of the United States of America.

Where is the real power in the United Nations? The real power in the United Nations is the power of the five permanent members of the Security Council - the United States, China, Russia, France, and the United Kingdom.
What is the basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue? The basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue is the muscle cell.
what is sarcomere? Sarcomere is a type of muscle fiber.
What is myofibril? Myofibril is a type of protein that helps muscles contract and move.

What is sarcoplasmic reticulum? Sarcoplasmic reticulum is a type of cell membrane that is found in the plasma membrane of cells. It is responsible for transporting proteins and other molecules across the cell membrane.
what is muscle fibre? Muscle fibre is the largest type of cell in the body and is responsible for moving the body's muscles. It is made up of long, thin cells that are filled with muscles' energy.
